other: This is one of those "different" cards, and I'm new to this, so it will need someone more expert to take a look at what I've done. , , There is information under the heading Circumstances, including the fact that the item must have been found prior to 1937, but I can't enter that as date of discovery., , Under "Description" it includes sections for Dimensions, Typology, Manufacture, Condition, Surface, Attached Material. , , I have tried to put the Dimensions info into the Length, Width, Edge and Thickness fields. However, several values were quoted for some of the dimensions e.g. Width. I assumed B stood for Breadth i.e. Thickness. I have no idea what DS stands for so I put that value into the Edge field., , I have put the Surface comments into the Surface field. , , I have put the Typology, Manufacture, Condition, and Attached Material info into the Description field., , Hard to read Abbrieviations: , , "e. bev."/"e. ber." (not sure which) crops up a couple of times. I have guessed at e.bev. (edge bevelled?), , "1p" or "lp". I have opted for "lp" (loop?)
